# Django Conventions

## Project Structure
- Use class-based views (CBV) for CRUD, function-based for complex logic
- All models in separate files: models/order.py, models/customer.py
- Use Django REST Framework for all API endpoints
- Write type hints for all function signatures
- Every model must have `__str__`, `Meta.ordering`, `verbose_name`

## Database
- Use select_related/prefetch_related to avoid N+1 queries
- Use django-filter for queryset filtering
- Prefer `F()` expressions over Python-side calculations
- Use `transaction.atomic()` for multi-model writes
- Index fields used in WHERE/ORDER BY clauses

## Models
- CharField max_length must be explicitly set
- Use `choices` for status fields (TextChoices enum)
- DateTimeField: use `auto_now_add` for created, `auto_now` for updated
- JSON fields: use `default=dict` not `default={}`
- ForeignKey: always set `on_delete` and `related_name`
- Decimal for money, never Float

## API (DRF)
- Use ModelViewSet + DefaultRouter
- Serializer per use case: ListSerializer (light), DetailSerializer (full)
- Pagination: CursorPagination for large datasets
- Permission classes per view
- Throttle rates for public endpoints

## Internationalization
- All text strings through `django.utils.translation` (gettext_lazy as _)
- Template strings via `{% trans %}` and `{% blocktrans %}`
- Default language: Russian (ru)
- Support: Armenian (hy), English (en)

## Async & Background Tasks
- Celery for background tasks (email, notifications, reports)
- Redis as broker and result backend
- Django Channels + WebSocket for real-time updates
- Task retry with exponential backoff

## Security
- CSRF protection on all forms
- Django security middleware enabled
- Sanitize user input, especially in JSON fields
- Rate limiting on authentication endpoints
- Never expose internal IDs in public URLs (use UUID or slug)

## Code Style
- ruff for linting, black for formatting
- Line length: 88 (black default)
- Import order: stdlib → django → third-party → local (isort)
- No wildcard imports
- Docstrings: Google style
